</HL>
<DATE>
09/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LUV
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Southwest Airlines said its August traffic rose
11% to 990 million revenue passenger miles from 894 million a
year earlier. A revenue passenger mile is one paying
passenger flown one mile.
   The airline's August load factor, or the percentage of
available seats occupied, rose to 68.4% from 67.4%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the first eight months of this year, Southwest's
traffic rose 6.7% to 6.79 billion revenue passenger miles
from 6.37 billion a year earlier. The load factor declined to
62.7% from 65.2%.
