<HL>
   Mapco Unit Defense Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
09/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B14
</SO>
<CO>
   MDA UNC SQAA GMH GM
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Mapco Alaska Petroleum Inc., a unit of Mapco
Inc., won an $82.5 million Defense Logistics Agency contract
for jet fuel.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   UNC Support Services, a unit of UNC Inc., got a $28.6
million Navy contract for helicopter maintenance.
                                                                                                       

   Turbocombustor Technology Inc., a unit of Sequa Corp.,
received a $17.1 million Air Force contract for jet engine
components.
                                                                                                       

   Crysen Refining Co. got a $16 million Defense Logistics
Agency contract for jet fuel.
                                                                                                       

   Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., was
awarded a $14.3 million Army contract for TOW missiles.
</TEXT>
