<LP>
   ST. PAUL, Minn. -- Northwest Airlines reported a monthly
record of 5.45 billion revenue passenger miles for August, an
8.3% increase from 5.03 billion miles flown in August 1989.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile. The NWA Inc. unit said its load factor, or percentage
of available seats filled, was unchanged at 76.8%.
