<HL>
   Raw-Steel Output Fell
   0.7% in Latest Week
</HL>
<DATE>
09/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Raw-steel production by the nation's mills
decreased 0.7% last week to 1,886,000 tons from 1,900,000
tons the previous week, the American Iron and Steel Institute
said.
   Last week's output rose 11.1% from the 1,697,000 tons
produced a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The industry used 84.5% of its capability last week,
compared with 85.1% the previous week and 76.4% a year ago.
                                                                                                       

   The American Iron and Steel Institute reported:
                                                                                                       

                               Net tons      Capability
                               produced      utilization
                                                                                                       

   Week to Sept. 8 .......      1,886,000      84.5%
   Week to Sept. 1 .......      1,900,000      85.1%
   Year to date ..........     67,997,000      84.6%
   Year earlier to date ..     69,063,000      86.7%
                                                                                                       

   The capability utilization rate is a calculation designed
to indicate at what percent of its production capability the
industry is operating in a given week.
</TEXT>
